## Bad examples

**Generic templated description (undesired -- near-duplicate content):**
"AIDE Architect is a powerful agent in the AIDE methodology pipeline."
"AIDE Implementor is a powerful agent in the AIDE methodology pipeline."
These differ only by the artifact name. A search engine will suppress them as near-duplicates.

**Marketing language in title (undesired -- violates voice constraints):**
"Unlock the Power of AIDE Spec -- Next-Gen AI-Native Engineering"
Words like "unlock," "power," "next-gen," and "AI-native" are prohibited.

**Fabricated structured data (undesired -- triggers manual actions):**
```json
{
  "@type": "TechArticle",
  "datePublished": "2024-01-01",
  "author": { "@type": "Person", "name": "John Doe" }
}
```
The date is invented (not sourced from content) and the author is a person who does not appear in the actual content. Both fields must trace to real data.

**Missing descriptions in llms.txt (undesired -- unusable by LLMs):**
```
## Agents
- AIDE Architect: https://aidemd.dev/agents/aide-architect
- AIDE Implementor: https://aidemd.dev/agents/aide-implementor
```
URLs without descriptions. An LLM cannot answer "what does the architect do?" from this file.

**Docs index that omits agents/commands/skills (undesired -- hides half the scaffold):**
A docs index that shows only:
```
- AIDE Spec
- AIDE Template
- Progressive Disclosure
- ...
```
This hides nine agents, twelve commands, and two skills from visitors and crawlers.

**Metadata that drifts from content (undesired -- promise mismatch):**
Title says "AIDE Spec -- Complete Reference Guide" but the page renders the raw aide-template.md content, which is a template, not a reference guide.

**Including .zed/ in the scaffold tree (undesired -- explicitly excluded):**
```
.zed/
  prompts/
    aide.md -> /zed/aide
```
The .zed/ folder must not appear anywhere in the scaffold tree.

